<div class="post-content">

<h2>Gameplay Mechanics</h2>
<p>Each night lasts 12 real-time minutes — double the length of a typical FNAF night. That extra time isn't padding; you need every second of it. Between monitoring cameras for red dots indicating critical rooms under threat, spinning around to pull levers on the control panel, managing your dwindling power supply, and dealing with ComCat's interruptions, NWAF keeps you in a constant state of controlled panic.</p>

<h3>The Animatronics</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Bonnie:</strong> Has four distinct attack routes. He can approach your left door directly, sabotage the compressor (disabling all remote doors in the building), attack the server room (killing your cameras), or sneak into Pirate's Cove to activate Foxy.</li>
    <li><strong>Chica:</strong> Also four attack methods. She targets the right door, the server room, Pirate's Cove to activate Foxy, or — most dangerously — the power grid, which shuts down everything and requires a full system restart.</li>
    <li><strong>Foxy:</strong> Doesn't act on his own. Bonnie or Chica must enter Pirate's Cove to wake him up. If Bonnie activates him, he charges left; if Chica, he goes right. Use the camera flash on Pirate's Cove to scare him back. If he reaches a closed door, he drains roughly 15% of your power.</li>
    <li><strong>Freddy (Night 4+):</strong> The ultimate threat. He can do everything Bonnie and Chica can, attack both doors, and access a second storage room to activate Scrap Foxy. He moves faster and hides in the shadows, making him harder to track on cameras.</li>
    <li><strong>Scrap Foxy:</strong> A deteriorated Foxy model stored in the second warehouse. When activated by another animatronic, he charges toward a random door and drains approximately 25% of your power on impact. The silver lining: he only attacks once per night.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Systems and Sabotage</h3>
<p>The real depth of NWAF comes from its interconnected systems. The compressor controls all remote doors — if an animatronic sabotages it, every door in the building swings open. The server room powers your cameras — lose it and you're blind. The power grid runs everything — a successful attack on it means total blackout until you manually restart each system, one by one, while animatronics roam freely.</p>

<p>Red dots on your camera feed warn you when an animatronic is approaching a critical room. When you spot one, you need to spin your chair around, find the correct lever on the control panel, and pull it before the sabotage succeeds. Miss the window and you're spending precious minutes on a manual restart while the others close in.</p>

</div>

